TY  - JOUR
TI  - Comparison of k-Class Estimators When the Disturbances Are Small
AU  - Kadane, Joseph B.
AB  - [A new approach to the choice of econometric estimators, called small-sigma asymptotics, is introduced and applied to the choice of k-class estimators of the parameters of a single equation in a system of linear simultaneous stochastic equations. I find that when the degree of overidentification is no more than six, the two stage least squares estimator uniformly dominates the limited information maximum likelihood estimator in a certain sense. The small sigma method can be used on many problems in statistics and econometrics.]
